##############################################
# MISSING KEYS - HOW TO GET THEM            #
##############################################

1. MONGODB_URI
   - Go to: https://cloud.mongodb.com
   - Create Atlas cluster (free tier available)
   - Database Access > Add User
   - Network Access > Add 0.0.0.0/0 (or Render IPs)
   - Connect > Get connection string

2. JWT_SECRET
   - Generate: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(64).toString('hex'))"
   - Or use: https://generate-secret.vercel.app/64

3. GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET 
   - You have GOOGLE_CLOUD_VISION_API_KEY but need OAuth secret
   - Go to: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
   - OAuth 2.0 Client IDs > Your client > Copy secret

4. SENDGRID_API_KEY (Optional - for emails)
   - Go to: https://sendgrid.com
   - Settings > API Keys > Create

5. CLOUDINARY (Optional - for file uploads)
   - Go to: https://cloudinary.com
   - Dashboard > Copy cloud name, API key, secret

##############################################
# PRIORITY ORDER FOR DEPLOYMENT             #
##############################################
1. Set MONGODB_URI first (critical)
2. Generate JWT_SECRET
3. Set FRONTEND_URL after creating frontend service
4. Test with minimal vars, add others as needed


